    "Background": {
      "text": "\"Donovanosis\"\nKlebsiella granulomatis\n: Intracellular gram negative rod\nSexually transmitted disease\nTropical and semitropical (India, Papua New Guinea, Australia, Carribean, Africa)\nVery rare in the United States",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Sexually transmitted disease",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Sexually_transmitted_disease"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Genital/perineal ulcer\nChronic, painless, progressive\nIrregular, clean-based, granulomatous, nodular\nHard, bleeds easily\n\"Beefy red\"\nInguinal lymphadenopathy is generally mild or absent\nUrethral stenosis\nLymphatic obstruction, elephantiasis\nHematogenous spread to spleen, lungs, liver, bones, orbits",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
